        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ee59a6/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2022-08-08T23:35:17.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello friends -<br>\nI recently purchased two bottles of Charles Noellat Santenay (Burgundy) from K&amp;L Wine in California.  Admittedly, I knew little about the producer but was rather drawn to the appellation (I love the subtleties of Santenay pinot) and the age on the bottles.  Neither are notable vintages but my curiosity was still piqued.  Sadly, there is little information out there regarding the producer in relation to these specific bottles. Noellat is of course a well known family in the region, but details on these bottles are hazy at best.  Is anyone familiar with them and, if so, what might have to look forward to??<br>\nThanks very much!<br>\nCheers ~<br>\n<img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/3/2/32ea8387b1b5bd4cf524d4a93aff3732a852fa6b.jpeg\" alt=\"IMG_2232.jpg\" data-base62-sha1=\"7gqjExFRJ6vholi83us0rSWBwin\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\"></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 5,
        "updated_at": "2022-08-15T21:46:56.617Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
